<F P=100> REGIONAL ECONOMIC AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhejiang Economic, Social Statistics </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhejiang Economic, Social Statistics </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0504044294 Hangzhou ZHEJIANG RIBAO in Chinese 13 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> OW0504044294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hangzhou ZHEJIANG RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by Zhejiang Provincial Bureau of </F>
Statistics on 8 March 1994: "Statistical Report on National 
Economic and Social Development"] 
  [Text] People in Zhejiang achieved noticeable success in 
reform, opening up, and economic construction as well as in 
strengthening and improving macroeconomic regulation and control 
in 1993, thanks to following through with the guidelines 
contained in Comrade Deng Xiaoping's important talks and the 
14th National CPC Congress; emancipating their minds; seeking 
truth from facts; and pressing forward with an exploratory 
spirit. People in the province enjoyed fast economic growth, 
social prosperity and progress, political unity and stability, 
and better living standards. According to preliminary 
statistics, the province's gross domestic product [GDP] 
increased 25 percent, reaching 164.5 billion yuan. Of this 
increase, the value of secondary industries increased 38.5 
percent, reaching 97.5 billion yuan; and the value of tertiary 
industries increased 14.4 percent, reaching 39 billion yuan. 
Noteworthy economic problems were the substantial rise in market 
prices; conspicuous shortage of funds; some enterprises' 
inability to withstand changes in the external environment; and 
a fairly weak agricultural foundation as the establishment of 
rural markets failed to keep pace with development. 
1. Agriculture [subhead] 
  Agricultural production went through the severe test of the 
removal of control over grain purchasing and marketing as well 
as grain prices, and the test was used as an opportunity to 
accelerate structural reform. Gratifying results were achieved 
in promoting high output of quality agricultural products 
yielding high returns. In 1993, the value of agricultural 
production increased 39 billion yuan, or 1.9 percent higher than 
that a year before. 
  The mix of agricultural products was readjusted quite 
substantially, and more foodgrain of good quality was produced. 
Of the output of major agricultural products, the output of 
fruits, sugarcane, and tea was higher than that of the preceding 
year. However, because of a relatively weak agricultural 
foundation, the output of grain, cotton, and other major 
agricultural crops declined in one way or another. 


