<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agriculture Delegation Departs for U.S. Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agriculture Delegation Departs for U.S. Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1004045394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0230 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1004045394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 10 (XINHUA) -- A government 
agriculture delegation led by Chinese Minister of Agriculture 
Liu Jiang left here this morning on a two-week official visit to 
the United States at the invitation of the U.S. secretary of 
agriculture. 
  The delegation will discuss with the American side exchanges 
of agro-technology and cooperation in agriculture so as to help 
promote an all-round growth of Sino-U.S. relations. 

