  [Text] Beijing, April 8 (XINHUA) -- A Chinese Foreign 
Ministry spokesman said here today that Japanese Prime Minister 
Morohiro Hosokawa's resignation is the internal affair of Japan. 
  When asked to make a reaction to Hosokawa's resignation, the 
spokesman said: "We've taken note of this news. This is the 
internal affair of Japan. 
  "Prime Minister Hosokawa has made precious efforts for 
promoting the development of the friendly relations between 
China and Japan. We hope that the Sino-Japanese relations will 
continue to develop steadily and soundly," he added. 

