<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] The Ministry of Economic Affairs has announced 
plans to bar ROC [Republic of China] investors, for the time 
being, from sinking further amounts of capital into the 
development of industrial parks in the mainland. The general 
disgust with conditions on the mainland enlisted by the boat 
tragedy may furnish the harsh warning ROC economic planners have 
been looking for to cool mainland investment fever. 

